{Black seems to be doing something on the queenside. How to react?} 9. h4 $1 {
In opposite-side castling middlegames, time is of the essence. We do not care
about the pawn on a2.} b4 10. Nb1 {h5 is coming up next and there is nothing
much that Black can do.} Qxa2 (10... Be6 11. Bxg7 Kxg7 12. h5 $18) (10... Nbd7
11. h5 $18) (10... Ba6 11. Bxa6 Nxa6 12. h5 Nc7 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Ne2 $16 {
We want to take and go Qh6 next. e5 is always in the air.}) 11. h5 Nbd7 12.
hxg6 fxg6 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Qh6+ Kf7 15. e5 $1 {We want to open up the center
too now.} dxe5 16. Nh3 Ke8 17. Ng5 $18 {There are many ways to continue for us.
We can bring our rook to e1 and Black is in a lot of trouble with the king on
e8.} *

