{How to continue here?} 9. a4 $1 {This was a surprising idea for me here as we
have usually been focussed on the kingside. Black was ready to meet the move
h4 but he has kept his bishop passive on the queenside. We are very flexible
with the king still in the center.} (9. h4 $6 Bxh6 10. Qxh6 Ng4 $1 11. Qd2 Ndf6
) 9... b4 10. Ne2 a5 11. Bxg7 Kxg7 12. Ng3 {Now we want to go h4-h5.} e5 13.
Qg5 $1 (13. h4 $6 Ng4 $1) 13... exd4 14. Nf5+ Kg8 15. Nxd6 $16 {Our knight is
well placed on d6 and we can continue with h4 or Bc4. We have a nice edge here.
} *

