{How to continue here?} 15. Bf2 $1 $146 {This has never been played before but
it is a very strong regrouping of pieces that I discovered when I was
analysing these files recently. The queen is perfect on the e3 square.} h6 (
15... Bg4 {Black goes after our d4 pawn.} 16. Ne4 $1 Bxf3 17. Nxf6+ {We
eliminate the dangerous dark-squared bishop and we enjoy the pair of bishops.}
Rxf6 18. Bxf3 $16 {Bh4 is a big threat now and Black is not in time to win the
pawn on c4.}) 16. Qe3 $1 Bh7 17. h3 $16 {We can continue with improving moves
such as b3, Kh1. Two ideas for us are to play Ne4 or Bd3 trading the bishops.}
*

