{How to continue here?} 7. Qd2 $1 {I just want to keep emphasising that we
should go for the initiative against such lines. Here we will castle queenside
and try to make use of the dark squared weaknesses on the kingside.} O-O (7...
c6 8. Bh6 $1) 8. Bh6 {We do not even waste a second to castle queenside. Next,
we can take a call to either go for h4-h5 directly or castle first. I will
give a few sample lines here.} Nc6 (8... c5 9. d5 Qd6 10. O-O-O $16) (8... Qd6
9. h4 Bg4 (9... Bf5 10. O-O-O {[%cal Gh4h5]}) 10. Bxg7 Kxg7 11. Ne5 $16) (8...
c6 9. h4 $1 Bg4 10. Bxg7 Kxg7 11. Ne5 h5 12. f3 Be6 13. O-O-O $14 {[%cal Gd2g5,
Gg2g4]}) 9. O-O-O Nb4 (9... Bg4 10. d5 $16) 10. h4 Bg4 11. h5 $1 {Our only aim
is to blast open the kingside.} Bxh5 12. Bxg7 (12. Rh4 $5 $16) 12... Kxg7 13.
d5 c6 14. g4 $1 Nxg4 15. Rxh5 gxh5 16. Qd4+ e5 17. Qxb4 $16 *

