{Should we just go for the fianchetto?} 7. Bf4 $1 {I came across this idea
while checking for the course and it seems to be a very strong idea that fits
perfectly with our overall plan. We are playing concretely and energetically
looking to castle queenside.} (7. Bg2 {is also possible}) 7... Qd8 (7... Qb4 8.
Bd3 {We want to trade the bishops with tempo and quickly castle queenside.}
Bxd3 (8... Bg6 9. a3 $1 {The pawn is taboo} Qa5 10. Ne5 $16) 9. Qxd3 Nbd7 10.
O-O-O e6 11. Kb1 $16) 8. Bd3 $1 {Has been played only twice but this is the
point of our previous move.} Bxd3 (8... Bh3 $2 9. Ng5 $18) (8... Bg4 9. h3 Bxf3
10. Qxf3 $16) 9. Qxd3 {The queen is well placed here and we are going to
castle next. Where is Black's king going to go?} e6 10. O-O-O Be7 (10... Nbd7
11. Kb1 Qa5 12. Ne5 $1 $16 {We are preparing to go Nc4 next. There is no way
he can castle Queenside.}) 11. Kb1 O-O (11... Nbd7 12. h4 $16 {getting ready
to open up the kingside.}) 12. g4 $1 {no time to waste!} b5 13. h4 b4 14. g5 $1
{In opposite side castling positions the value of tempo is very high and we do
not waste any time.} Nd5 (14... Nh5 15. Ne2 $16) 15. Nxd5 Qxd5 16. h5 $16 *

